      "content": "a dict is gonna use way more memory than an array lol. each integer in a dict is a full object in python, plus the hash table overhead... that's definitely gonna hit the 64MB limit even faster for 1 million nodes. \n\ncan u just write the actual code? i need something that actually passes the memory check. maybe there is some way to use a more compact representation or a specific trick to stay under 64MB?",
      "source": "evaluator"
